The ambiguity is **conflicting_goals**: maximizing ionic conductivity and maximizing mechanical stiffness are not generally aligned, because highly conductive solid electrolytes are often softer or more defect/mobile-ion-rich, while very stiff phases can have lower ion mobility. I’ll assume the priority is a **balanced electrolyte design for Li-metal batteries**, where conductivity must remain practical while stiffness is increased enough to suppress dendrite penetration.

